  "local_port": 41212,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How much does it cost to register a trademark in the U.S.?",
  "response": "Registering a trademark in the United States involves several costs, which can vary based on factors like the number of classes of goods or services, whether you use an attorney, and additional services such as trademark searches. Here's a breakdown of the primary costs associated with registering a trademark with the United States Patent and Trademark Office (USPTO):\n\n### 1. **USPTO Filing Fees**\nThe USPTO offers different application forms, each with its own fee structure:\n\n- **TEAS Plus Application:**\n  - **Cost:** **$250 per class** of goods/services\n  - **Requirements:** This option requires you to meet specific filing requirements, such as selecting from a predefined list of goods/services. It's less expensive but less flexible.\n\n- **TEAS Standard Application:**\n  - **Cost:** **$350 per class** of goods/services\n  - **Flexibility:** Allows for a broader description of goods/services but comes at a higher cost.\n\n> **Note:** Choosing the right application type depends on your specific needs and the complexity of your trademark. Most applicants find TEAS Plus to be cost-effective if their goods/services fit the predefined categories.\n\n### 2. **Trademark Search Fees**\nBefore filing, conducting a comprehensive trademark search is advisable to ensure that your desired trademark isn't already in use or registered. While a search isn't mandatory, it can save you time and money by identifying potential conflicts early.\n\n- **DIY Search:** Free using the [USPTO\u2019s TESS](https://www.uspto.gov/trademarks/search) (Trademark Electronic Search System), though it may not be exhaustive.\n- **Professional Search Services:** **$100 to $1,000+**\n  - **Benefits:** Comprehensive search reports, legal analysis, and peace of mind.\n\n### 3. **Attorney Fees**\nWhile it's possible to file a trademark application on your own, many applicants choose to hire a trademark attorney to navigate the complexities of trademark law, respond to USPTO communications, and ensure the application is properly filed.\n\n- **Cost Range:** **$500 to $2,000+**\n  - **Factors Influencing Cost:** Complexity of the trademark, number of classes, attorney\u2019s experience, and additional services like handling oppositions or office actions.\n\n### 4. **Additional USPTO Fees**\nDepending on the specifics of your application and post-registration requirements, you might encounter additional fees:\n\n- **Statement of Use Filing:**\n  - **Cost:** **$100 per class** (if you filed based on intent to use)\n  \n- **Extension of Time to File Statement of Use:**\n  - **Cost:** **$125 per class**\n\n- **Renewal Fees:**\n  - **Between the 5th and 6th year:** **$425 per class**\n  - **Between the 9th and 10th year:** **$425 per class**\n  - **Every 10 years thereafter:** **$525 per class**\n\n### 5. **Responding to USPTO Office Actions**\nIf the USPTO has questions or requires additional information regarding your application, responding to an Office Action may incur additional costs, especially if handled by an attorney.\n\n- **Attorney Fees for Responses:** **$200 to $1,000+** depending on the complexity\n\n### **Estimated Total Costs**\nFor a straightforward trademark application in one class without complications:\n\n- **DIY Approach:**\n  - **USPTO Fees:** $250 (TEAS Plus) or $350 (TEAS Standard)\n  - **Optional Search:** $0 (DIY) to ~$500 (professional)\n  - **Total Estimated Cost:** **$250 to $850**\n\n- **Using an Attorney:**\n  - **USPTO Fees:** $250 to $350\n  - **Attorney Fees:** $500 to $2,000+\n  - **Trademark Search:** $100 to $1,000+\n  - **Total Estimated Cost:** **$850 to $3,350+**\n\n### **Additional Considerations**\n- **Multiple Classes:** If your trademark covers multiple classes of goods or services, costs increase per class.\n- **International Registration:** If you plan to register your trademark in other countries, additional costs and processes apply.\n- **Maintenance:** Remember that maintaining a registered trademark requires periodic filings and fees to keep the registration active.\n\n### **Final Tips**\n- **Do Thorough Research:** Investing in a comprehensive trademark search can save you from potential legal disputes and additional costs down the line.\n- **Consider Professional Assistance:** While it's possible to navigate the USPTO process alone, professional guidance can enhance the likelihood of successful registration, especially for complex trademarks.\n- **Budget for Ongoing Costs:** Beyond initial registration, plan for maintenance fees to protect your trademark in the long term.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, always refer to the [official USPTO fee schedule](https://www.uspto.gov/learning-and-resources/fees-and-payment/uspto-fee-schedule) or consult with a trademark attorney.",
  "response_tokens": [
